I like the game. Really do, except for one small issue: Casting spells! Do you know how hard it is to draw a bloody star with your fingure? Especially when you have zero artistic abilities to begin with, it ain't easy.   And don't even get me started with the fire. I believe those two symbols are way to complex for the game to acknowledge that you actual drew them, even when you have! I would have been just as happy,with a triangle or an "X" or any other basic symbol. Also,the amount of time allotted to draw them, by which I mean actually drawing the symbol, is way to short. How am I suppose to draw an object like that super fast when it has that mean curves and turns with the need of incorporating precision. Maybe other people have that skill, but I sure don't.  Love the changes to the story, although they aren't as funny as I remember. Least there was no attempt in some crappy voice-over like the 7th Lego Star Wars tried to do - if you haven't played it, go play it. Its hilarious how poor of a job it was even if all you had to work with was movie clips. But as always, the gameplay itself is good which is what you can expect from a Warner Bros game.  Anyways, all in all I enjoy the game. No major complains.

A solid port of an excellent game. I had fond memories playing this on the PSP and DS back then and being able to experience it again on my android after it's been on iOS for so long is an absolute delight. However the controls feel about stiff and wonky, it's not game breaking but coming from the DS stylus and PSP analog stick, I have to say it's not as fluid on my Z3 Compact. The game however hasn't changed and the gaming experience is great. Smooth buttery framerates no hitches and stutters and loading times are good. Only gripe about the game play is that it won't play in full screen. I get this weird sort of 4:3 aspect ratio during gameplay. Hopefully it will be patched out. But great job on the port nonetheless lads.
